Usage:

chmod +x install-tds.sh
sudo ./install-tds.sh


This will:

Download TDS

Install in /opt/technitium-dns

Set up a systemd service that starts on boot

Start the server automatically

Usage:

chmod +x update-tds.sh
sudo ./update-tds.sh


This will:

Stop the running service

Backup your current installation

Download the latest TDS version

Overwrite binaries but keep Data/ and config intact

Restart the service

✅ Notes / Tips

Make sure port 53 is free (UDP/TCP) before running

The web UI is always at http://<server-ip>:5380/

You can add extra upstream DNS servers and blocklists via the web UI

These scripts are reusable — you can run update-tds.sh whenever a new release comes out
